!! What it does

Adds a ''Rimi Plugins'' top-level tab to the ControlPanel. The tab shows a vertical sidebar listing all installed rimir plugins, with a content area that displays each plugin's settings panel or a default info card.

!! Features

* ''Dynamic discovery'' — automatically lists all plugins with title prefix `$:/plugins/rimir/`
* ''Vertical sidebar'' — click any plugin to view its settings; active plugin highlighted with accent border
* ''Auto-selection'' — first plugin selected on load (no blank content)
* ''Fallback panel'' — plugins without settings show an info card with a link to documentation
* ''Dual-purpose settings'' — the same `settings` tiddler appears both in the hub and in TW's built-in plugin detail view

!! How plugins opt in

Create a tiddler titled `$:/plugins/rimir/<slug>/settings` inside your plugin. The hub transcludes it as the content panel. Add `"settings"` to the `list` field in `plugin.info` so TW's plugin info view also shows a settings tab.

</$fill>
